<DocsPageTitle Path="Components/BreakpointObserver" AddedVersion="Added in v2.1">
    Blazorise BreakpointObserver component
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Render different content at runtime based on the current responsive breakpoint.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    <Code Tag>BreakpointObserver</Code> listens to the shared responsive breakpoint service and re-renders its child content whenever the current breakpoint changes. Use it when the markup or behavior needs to change at runtime, not just the CSS classes.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    If you only need styling changes, prefer regular responsive utility classes. Use <Code Tag>BreakpointObserver</Code> when you need to switch layouts, controls, or content based on the active breakpoint.
</DocsPageParagraph>

